<item>
            <title>[LU-17666] configure lnet before add net in sanity-sec:31</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17666</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity-sec:31 fails with error of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;sanity-sec test_31: @@@@@@ FAIL: unable to configure NID on tcp999 for node test01&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; Trace dump:&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6646:error()&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity-sec.sh:2561:test_31()&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6981:run_one()&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:7031:run_one_logged()&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6869:run_test()&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity-sec.sh:2647:main()&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The reason is, Lnet has not been configured yet when the test script tries to run command &quot;/usr/sbin/lnetctl net add --if eth1 --net tcp999&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maloo does not hit this problem, probably because &quot;options lnet config_on_load=1&quot; is configured for Lnet module.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
